                    <span>Jeffrey Gitomer makes some good points but nothing I haven't seen before in his weekly columns or "Sales Caffeine". I was surprised at how short/small the book was and even more surprised when I saw the extensive use of large fonts, short chapters and wide margins. This is more like an 75 page book - not 130. The main thing that I got out of it was a desire to learn more about John Patterson -- he was an intriguing guy.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Very uneven</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>4</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
                      <span>3</span>
                      /
                      <span>3</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
